            Of course, some of these
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">nuggets</ENAMEX> are ambiguous. Thus, we have <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Swedish Count Axel Oxenstierna</ENAMEX> writing in
the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">17 th century</TIMEX>, "<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Behold</ENAMEX>, my <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">son</ENAMEX>, with how little wisdom the world
is governed." For <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">a long time</TIMEX> I thought that this was a complaint that the
