may not be the best policy, but it is worth trying once in a while .

            --<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richard Nixon</ENAMEX>, in a
meeting, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1970</TIMEX>

            This may seem the ultimate
in cynicism, but the second half of the quotation (about trying honesty once in
a while) seems foreign to many <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">politicians</ENAMEX>, among others.

             

            
               Surely
there is something unlovely, to modern as against medieval minds, about marked
inequality of either <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">kind</ENAMEX> [income or power].

            --<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry C. Simons</ENAMEX>,
